						<summary>

						<p>Broken slab leaning against the south wall near the <hi rend="italic">hōmakunḍa</hi> in the Pañchaliṅgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>1363 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged and broken record refers to a gift probably to god Mārkaṇḍēśvara-dēva. The details are all, however, lost. It refers to <hi rend="italic">mahāpradhāna</hi> <hi rend="bold">Maleya-daṇṇāyaka</hi> as governing <hi rend="bold">Bārakūru-rājya.</hi></p>						

						<p>It is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1285, Sōbhakṛit, Kārttika śu. 8, Sunday</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1363 A.D., October 15, Sunday, f.d.t. ·15.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
